 Port Elizabeth - The Anti-Gang Unit Tracking team arrested a 27-year-old male while they were busy tracing for wanted suspects in Bethelsdorp, Port Elizabeth. "It is alleged that on Thursday, at about 11:20, while the team were in Acclipia Street, in Kleinskool, they spotted two known gang members," said police spokesperson, Col Priscilla Naidu. "They stopped and searched them and a 9mm firearm and two rounds were found in the left side pocket of one of the suspects." He was arrested and detained on a charge of illegal possession of a firearm and ammunition. "Ownership of the firearm is yet to be determined," she added. "The suspect is expected to appear in court soon." Follow more RNEWS articles, subscribe to our YouTube channel and for breaking news LIKE us on Facebook. For news on the Western Cape click here. For great savings on life’s little pleasures visit Bargain Buys!  Know somebody who is getting married, Wedding and Function can assist.  Have kids, then you need to visit Kids Connection. Enjoy food and travel, then visit Home Food and Travel. Need assistance with an online presence, visit Agency One. 